Signal: Check out cal.com. It's an open-source calendar service that integrates features such as scheduling Element and Jitsi video calls. It also supports Signal, but I haven't tested it yet to see if it's just for messaging or for video calls as well.
I can recommend @user6. End-to-end encryption, decentralized, open-source.
